  "id": "volatility_compression_reversal_strategy",
  "name": "Volatility Compression Reversal Strategy",
  "description": "This strategy identifies trading opportunities based on volatility compression using Bollinger Bands. It enters long positions when the price closes above the upper band with increased volume, and short positions when the opposite conditions are met, capitalizing on potential reversals after periods of low volatility.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Develop a strategy that trades reversals after volatility compression. Identify periods where the 14-period Bollinger Bands width is at a 6-month (126 trading days) low, indicating prolonged price consolidation. Enter a long position when price closes above the upper Bollinger Band *and* the day\u2019s volume is at least 50% greater than the 20-period average volume. Enter a short position when price closes below the lower Bollinger Band with the same volume condition. Exit positions when price returns to the 20-period moving average or after 10 trading days, whichever comes first. No position should be open if the Bollinger Band width is not at its 126-day minimum.",
